#12511
At New Hope Castle~
You stand outside of New Hope Castle, a giant white-stone walled
castle, more wide then tall, spanning a great distance abroad,
and probably goes far back as well.  The door is left open in the
daytime, and the drawbridge dropped down for people to cross the
moat, and many do, coming back and forth in their business.
Towers protrude from the wall on either side of you, with a minimal
amount of guards posted high above on the walls in watch in these
times of peace.
~
You stand outside of New Hope Castle, a giant white-stone walled
castle, more wide then tall, spanning a great distance abroad,
and probably goes far back as well.  The doors to the castle are
open during night, but the drawbridge raised so the castle can
be left quiet during night time.
Towers protrude from the wall on either side of you, with no more
guards posted in watch high above on the walls then during day
time, since in these more peaceful days there is little need for
such men.
~
